&lt;h2 id="part-1">Part 1&lt;/h2>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>Given a series of robots defined with initial &lt;code>position&lt;/code> and &lt;code>velocity&lt;/code> on a 101x103 &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/toroidal">toroidal&lt;/a> grid, calculate where the robots will be after 100 iterations. Return the product of the number of robots in each &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/quadrant">quadrant&lt;/a> of the final grid, ignoring the middle lines (since they&amp;rsquo;re odd).&lt;/p>&lt;/blockquote></description></item></channel></rss>